    "B. Ablation Study on Different Evaluation SettingsIn this section, we explore the performance of fine-tuned models using varying data formats in both the training and evaluation phases.",
    "Although high-level global summaries are the most user-friendly data format, their ambiguity often results in a lack of detailed information necessary for preciseTABLE I: Comparison across fine-tuning and evaluation data formats using the CodeLLaMA-7B-Instruct model.",
    "The table columns indicate the data formats used for fine-tuning, while the rows show the formats used during evaluation.",
    "Performance is color-coded for clarity: warm colors (red and orange) indicate high performance, while cool colors (light blue and blue) denote lower performance.",
    "The color gradient from best to worst performance is as follows: red (highest), orange, light blue, and blue (lowest)."
